  "texts": [
    "In a focused evaluation involving 200 random cases where GPT-4 and provider-assigned ICD codes did not exactly match, the human reviewers (two attendings and two residents) were blindly tasked with rating the accuracy of each assignment (Figure 5a).",
    "GPT-4 consistently demonstrated superior accuracy.",
    "GPT-4's performance ranged from 1.23 to 2.69 times better than providers, with the largest difference observed with Resident 1 (129 for GPT-4 vs. 48 for human).",
    "Overall, reviewers preferred GPT-4 for accuracy in 447 cases, compared to 277 cases where human coders were preferred (p<0.001).",
    "The results of the physicians' evaluation of code assignment specificity of GPT-4 vs. provider coders are presented in Figure 5b."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}